|\u22123\n|-\n| align=center|{{silver02}} || {{GBR2}} 3 || 72-70=142 || align=center|\u22122\n|-\n| align=center|{{bronze03}} || {{SWE}} 2 || 70-73=143 || rowspan=2 align=center|\u22121\n|-\n| align=center|4 || {{ESP}} || 75-68=143\n|-\n| rowspan=2 align=center|T5 || {{GBR2}} 1 || 76-69=145 || rowspan=2 align=center|+1\n|-\n| {{SWE}} 1 || 72-73=145\n|-\n| align=center|7 || {{AUT}} || 75-72=147 || align=center|+3\n|-\n| align=center|8 || {{BEL}} || 77-71=148 || align=center|+4\n|-\n| rowspan=2 align=center|T9 || {{GBR2}} 2 || 76-73=149 || rowspan=2 align=center|+5\n|-\n| {{NOR}} || 73-76=149\n|-\n| align=center|11 || {{ITA}} || 76-74=150 || align=center|+6\n|}\nSweden 2 defeated Spain with a birdie at the first hole of the bronze medal playoff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europeantour.com/europeantour/season=2018/tournamentid=2018067/news/newsid=354758.html |title=Ice-cool Iceland win gold in mixed event |publisher=PGA European Tour |date=11 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|labelwidth=100|width=170}}\n|-\n|Men's team\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} '''Spain 1'''<br>[[Pedro Oriol]]<br>[[Scott Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n| {{flagicon|ISL}} '''Iceland'''<br>[[Birgir Haf\u00fe\u00f3rsson]]<br>[[Axel B\u00f3asson]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} '''Italy 2'''<br> [[Francesco Laporta]]<br>[[Alessandro Tadini]]\n|-\n|Women's team\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} '''Sweden 3'''<br>[[Cajsa Persson]]<br>[[Linda Wessberg]]\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} '''France 2'''<br>[[Justine Dreher]]<br>[[Manon Moll\u00e9]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} '''Great Britain 3'''<br>[[Meghan MacLaren]]<br>[[Michele Thomson]]\n|-\n| [[2018 European Golf Team Championships - Mixed team|Mixed team]]\n| {{flagicon|ISL}} '''Iceland'''<br />[[\u00d3laf\u00eda \u00de\u00f3runn Kristinsd\u00f3ttir]]<br />[[Birgir Haf\u00fe\u00f3rsson]]<br />[[Valdis Thora Jonsdottir]]<br />[[Axel B\u00f3asson]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} '''Great Britain 3'''<br />[[Meghan MacLaren]] <br /> [[Liam Johnston (golfer)|Liam Johnston]]<br />[[Michele Thomson]]<br />[[Connor Syme]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} '''Sweden 2'''<br />[[Daniel Jennevret]]<br />[[Oscar Flor\u00e9n]]<br />[[Johanna Gustavsson]]<br />[[Julia Engstr\u00f6m]]\n|}\n\n==Medal summary== \n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = GBR\n | flag_template  = \n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_ISL = 1 | silver_ISL = 1 | bronze_ISL = 0\n | gold_SWE = 1 | silver_SWE = 0 | bronze_SWE = 1\n | gold_ESP = 1 | silver_ESP = 0 | bronze_ESP = 0\n | gold_GBR = 0 | silver_GBR = 1 | bronze_GBR = 1 | host_GBR = yes\n | gold_FRA = 0 | silver_FRA = 1 | bronze_FRA = 0\n | gold_ITA = 0 | silver_ITA = 0 | bronze_ITA = 1\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{OfficialSite|https://www.europeanchampionships.com/sports/golf}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20180730234601/https://www.glasgow2018.com/sports/golf European Championships Glasgow 2018 site]\n*[https://www.europeanchampionships.com/ECG2018/en/results-books/download/EC2018%20Golf%20Results%20Book.pdf Results book \u2212 Golf]\n*[http://www.europeantour.com/europeantour/season=2018/tournamentid=2018067/index.html Coverage on the European Tour site]\n*[https://ladieseuropeantour.com/tournament-page/?tourn=1810&season=2018 Coverage on the Ladies European Tour site]\n\n{{2018 European Championships}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:European Golf Team Championships}}\n[[Category:2018 European Golf Team Championships| ]]\n[[Category:Team golf tournaments]]\n[[Category:Golf tournaments in Scotland|2018 European Golf Team Championships]]\n[[Category:Sport in Perth and Kinross|2018 European Golf Team Championships]]\n[[Category:2018 European Championships|Golf]]\n[[Category:2018 in golf]]\n[[Category:2018 in Scottish sport]]\n[[Category:August 2018 sports events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox individual golf tournament\n| name          = 2018 European Golf Team Championships\n| image         = 2018 European Golf Team Championships Logo.svg\n| caption       = \n| dates         = 8\u201312 August 2018\n| location      = [[Auchterarder]], [[Scotland]], U.K.\n| course        = [[Gleneagles Hotel#Golf|PGA Centenary Course, Gleneagles]]\n| lang          = \n| org           = \n| tour          = [[European Tour]]<br>[[Ladies European Tour]]\n| format        = Men's/women's team \u2013 [[match play]]<br>Mixed team \u2013 18-hole [[stroke play]]\n| par           = 72\n| yardage       = \n| field         = 68 players from 15 nations<br><small>16 two-player teams \u2013 men's<br>16 two-player teams \u2013 women's<br>11 four-player teams \u2013 mixed</small>\n| cut           = <!-- None -->\n| purse         = \u20ac500,000 \u2013 Men's team<br>\u20ac500,000 \u2013 Women's team<br>\u20ac95,000 \u2013 Mixed team<ref name=oneweek/>\n| winners_share =  \n| champion      =  \n| score         =  \n| previous      = Inaugural\n| next          = [[2022 European Golf Team Championships|2022]]\n| map           = UK#UK Scotland\n| map_relief    = yes\n| map_label     = <small>Auchterarder</small>\n| map_caption   = Location in the [[United Kingdom]]##Location in [[Scotland]]\n| coordinates   = {{coord|56.2834|-3.7522|type:event|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n{{2018 European Golf Team Championships}}\n\nThe '''2018 European Golf Team Championships''' was a golf tournament played in August 2018 at [[Gleneagles, Scotland]]. It was the inaugural event and consisted of three competitions \u2013 men's, women's and mixed team format. 16 two-player teams took part in both men's and women's competitions.<ref name=teams>{{cite web |url=http://www.europeantour.com/europeantour/season=2018/tournamentid=2018067/news/newsid=352569.html |title=Teams unveiled for historic European Golf Team Championships |publisher=PGA European Tour |date=16 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe event was part of the [[2018 European Championships]], the inaugural edition of the [[European Championships]], a multi-sport event which took place in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]], and [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]] from 2 to 12 August 2018.\n\n'''Iceland''' topped the medal table, with a surprise win in the mixed team event the highlight of a campaign that returned two medals. Hosts '''Great Britain''' and '''Sweden''' both returned two medals, the latter including the gold in the women's team event, while '''Spain''' triumphed in the men's team.\n\n==Format==\nThe European Golf Team Championships took place at Gleneagles in Scotland from 8\u221212 August 2018, featuring a 50/50 gender split in the field with male and female professionals competing for equal prize money in a men's team [[match play]] championship, a women's team match play championship, and a mixed team 18-hole foursomes [[stroke play]] championship.\n\nThe field consisted of 16 teams of two players competing in the men's and women's team events, before combining to form teams of four (two men and two women) in the mixed team championship.\n\nThe men's and women's team championships featured a round-robin group [[Four-ball golf|fourball]] format, on 8\u201310 August, with winners of each of the four groups progressing to the semi-finals where [[Foursome (golf)|foursomes]] will determine the winners, on 12 August. In the group stage, two points were awarded for a win, one point for a halved match, and no points for a loss. Ties between two teams in the standings were determined by their head-to-head result and if teams were still tied for first place then a sudden-death playoff would occur.<ref name=oneweek/><ref name=sched>{{cite web |url=https://www.europeanchampionships.com/results/en/golf/daily-schedule.htm |title=Golf \u2013 Daily Schedule |publisher=European Championships |access-date=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe mixed team championship comprised teams of four (2 men and 2 women) playing in 18-hole mixed foursomes stroke play on 11 August, with combined scores used for team's total score. Ties for medal positions were determined by a sudden-death playoff involving the low-scoring foursome from each team involved.<ref name=oneweek/><ref name=sched/>\n\n==Qualification==\nQualification for the Championships was via the European Golf Team Championships points tables for men and women, which were based on men's [[Official World Golf Ranking]] points and women's [[Women's World Golf Rankings]] points earned from tournaments finishing between 10 July 2017 and 9 July 2018 with a maximum of three teams representing any one nation in each event.<ref name=teams/>\n\n==Competitors==\nThe following competitors were announced for the championships.<ref name=oneweek>{{cite web |url=https://ladieseuropeantour.com/one-week-to-go-teams-finalised-for-european-golf-team-championships/ |title=One Week To Go \u2013 Teams Finalised For European Golf Team Championships |publisher=Ladies European Tour |date=1 August 2018}}</ref> Rank is the [[Official World Golf Ranking]] (men) or [[Women's World Golf Rankings]] (women) in the week prior to the championship.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n===Men===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n! Seed !! Country !! Players (rank)\n|-\n| align=center|1 || {{GBR2}} 1 || [[Callum Shinkwin]] (230) & [[Lee Slattery]] (233)\n|-\n| align=center|2 || {{ITA}} 1 || [[Lorenzo Gagli]] (275) & [[Guido Migliozzi]] (593)\n|-\n| align=center|3 || {{ESP}} 1 || [[Pedro Oriol]] (355) & [[Scott Fern\u00e1ndez]] (476)\n|-\n| align=center|4 || {{GBR2}} 2 || [[Rhys Enoch]] (396) & [[Charlie Ford (golfer)|Charlie Ford]] (509)\n|-\n| align=center|5 || {{GBR2}} 3 || [[Connor Syme]] (322) & [[Liam Johnston]] (381)\n|-\n| align=center|6 || {{PRT}} || [[Jos\u00e9-Filipe Lima]] (341) & [[Ricardo Santos (golfer)|Ricardo Santos]] (738)\n|-\n| align=center|7 || {{NOR}} || [[Jarand Ekeland Arn\u00f8y]] (668) & [[Kristian Krogh Johannessen]] (493)\n|-\n| align=center|8 || {{ESP}} 2 || [[Santiago Tarr\u00edo]] (391) & [[David Borda]] (649)\n|-\n| align=center|9 || {{SWE}} 1 || [[Per L\u00e4ngfors]] (468) & [[Johan Edfors]] (759)\n|-\n| align=center|10