ticism of the accounts of the Oneida Community in \"New America,\" \"Spiritual wives\" and kindred publications |publisher=Oneida Community |year=1871 |oclc=1019550753 |url=https://hdl.handle.net/2027/umn.31951001556691t?urlappend=%3Bseq=41 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Noyes |first=Pierrepont B |title=My Father's House: An Oneida Boyhood |publisher=Farrar & Rinehart |publication-place=New York & Toronto |url=https://archive.org/details/myfathershouse0000unse/mode/2up |year=1937 |oclc=220609800 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Stoehr |first=Taylor |title=Free Love in America: A Documentary History |publisher=AMS Press |publication-place=New York |year=1979 |isbn=9780404160340 |oclc=4667712 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal |title=The Status and Self-Perception of Women in the Oneida Community |last=Wayland-Smith |first=Ellen |journal=Communal Societies. |publisher=National Historic Communal Societies Association (NHCSA) |year=1988 |issn=0739-1250 |volume=8 |pages=18-54 |oclc=880519344 |url=https://www.communalstudies.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/8.zip |format=PDF in ZIP |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Wonderley |first=Anthony |title=Oneida Utopia: A Community Searching for Human Happiness and Prosperity |publisher=Cornell University Press |publication-place=Ithaca, NY |year=2017 |isbn=9781501709807 |oclc=989726897 |ref=harv}} Limited preview: {{Google books|id=yNI6DwAAQBAJ|title=Oneida Utopia: A Community Searching for Human Happiness and Prosperity}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{Refbegin|30em}}\n*{{cite book |last=Barkun |first=Michael |authorlink=Michael Barkun |title=Crucible of the Millennium: The Burned-Over District of New York in the 1840s |publisher=Syracuse University Press |location=Syracuse, N.Y |year=1986 |isbn=9780815623717 |oclc=781774661 }} Limited preview: {{Google books|id=TorU47NdT5UC|title=Crucible of the Millennium: The Burned-Over District of New York in the 1840s}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Bernstein |first=Leonard |title=The Ideas of John Humphrey Noyes, Perfectionist |journal=American Quarterly |volume=5 |issue=2 |date=Summer 1953 |issn=0003-0678 |doi=10.2307/3031316 |oclc=5545646830 |pages=157\u2013165|jstor=3031316 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Carden |first=Maren |title=Oneida : Utopian community to modern corporation |publisher=Johns Hopkins Press |publication-place=Baltimore |year=1969 |isbn=9780801810190 |oclc=28166  |url=https://archive.org/details/oneidautopiancom00card}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Foster |first=Lawrence |title=Free Love and Feminism: John Humphrey Noyes and the Oneida Community |journal=Journal of the Early Republic |publisher=JSTOR |volume=1 |issue=2 |year=1981  |doi=10.2307/3123007 |pages=165\u2013183 |jstor=3123007 |oclc=7374820925 |issn=0275-1275}}\n* {{cite book |last=Foster |first=Lawrence |year=1981 |title=Religion and Sexuality: The Shakers, the Mormons, and the Oneida Community |publisher=University of Illinois Press |isbn=9780252011191 |url=https://archive.org/details/religionsexualit0000fost |url-access=registration |chapter=That All May Be One: John Humphrey Noyes and the Origins of Oneida Community Complex Marriage |pages=72\u2013122 |oclc=70453687 |location=Urbana, IL, US }}\n*{{cite book |last=Hinds |first=William Alfred |chapter=The Perfectionists and Their Communities |title=American communities and co-operative colonies |edition=2nd |publisher=University Press of the Pacific |location=Honolulu |year=2004 |orig-year=1908 |isbn=9781410211521 |oclc=609764632 |pages=152\u2013231 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/AmericanCommunitiesAndCo-operativeColonies/page/n397}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Kephart |first=William M. |title=Experimental Family Organization: An Historico-Cultural Report on the Oneida Community |journal=Marriage and Family Living |publisher=JSTOR |volume=25 |issue=3 |year=1963 |issn=0885-7059 |doi=10.2307/349069 |oclc=5548745504 |pages=261\u2013271|jstor=349069 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Klaw |first=Spencer |title=Without Sin: The Life and Death of the O