 Press |location=Amherst |year=1984 |isbn=9780585083889 |oclc=43475558 |url=https://archive.org/details/religionsocietyu00iral}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Meyer |first=William B. |title=The Perfectionists and the Weather: The Oneida Community's Quest for Meteorological Utopia, 1848-1879 |journal=Environmental History |publisher=Oxford University Press |volume=7 |issue=4 |date=October 2002 |pages=589\u2013610 |issn=1084-5453 |doi=10.2307/3986058 |jstor=3986058 |oclc=7025508514}}\n*{{cite book |last=Noyes |first=Pierrepont B. |title=A Goodly Heritage |publisher=Rinehart |location=New York|year=1958 |oclc=855124}}\n*{{cite journal |last=Olin |first=Spencer C. |title=The Oneida Community and the Instability of Charismatic Authority |journal=The Journal of American History |publisher=Oxford University Press (OUP) |volume=67 |issue=2 |year=1980 |issn=0021-8723 |doi=10.2307/1890409 |pages=285\u2013300 |jstor=1890409 |oclc=5545193702}}\n*{{cite web |last=Robertson |first=Constance Noyes |title=Oneida Community the breakup, 1876-1881 |publisher=Syracuse University Press |publication-place=Syracuse |year=1972 |isbn=9780815600862 |oclc=575871149 |url=https://archive.org/details/oneidacommunity00cons_0}}\n*{{cite web |last=Robertson |first=Constance Noyes |title=Oneida Community; An Autobiography 1851\u20131876 |publication-place=Syracuse, NY |publisher=Syracuse University Press |year=1970 |oclc=904188421 |url=https://archive.org/details/oneidacommunitya00robe |isbn=9780815600695}}\n*{{cite book |last=Ryan |first=Mary P. |authorlink=Mary P. Ryan |title=Cradle of the middle class : the family in Oneida County, New York, 1790-1865 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |publication-place=Cambridge, Eng. New York |year=1981 |isbn=9780521274036 |oclc=1029047763 |url=https://archive.org/details/cradleofmiddlecl00mary}}\n*{{cite book |last=Smith |first=Goldwin |authorlink=Goldwin Smith |chapter=The Oneida Community and American Socialism |title=Essays on questions of the day, political a